-- Japanese Sold Net 1144.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-04-10T23:55:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-10/japanese-sold-net-1144-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended April 5 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 1144.9 billion yen ($11.5 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 6.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 75.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 1063.1 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 463.6 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 868.6 billion yen in stocks, and bought 2429.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 3762
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
